genresAdvancedInfo.name: indie michoacano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre that blends traditional Mexican folk music with indie rock, creating a unique sound that is both nostalgic and modern. It often features acoustic instruments such as guitars and accordions, and incorporates lyrics in Spanish that touch on themes such as love, loss, and cultural identity.
